1
00:00:25,640 --> 00:00:27,200
Well...

2
00:00:29,646 --> 00:00:31,080
Well...

3
00:00:47,014 --> 00:00:52,432
Hello, students and parents.

4
00:00:53,655 --> 00:00:57,126
I'm Teacher Pobmek.

5
00:00:59,356 --> 00:01:01,222
Honestly...

6
00:01:02,340 --> 00:01:05,123
I don't know what to say today.

7
00:01:06,190 --> 00:01:11,020
So I'm just going to tell you a story.

8
00:01:15,595 --> 00:01:20,718
This story is about a man.

9
00:01:23,095 --> 00:01:25,017
He's a teacher.

10
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:34,100
A teacher is supposed to love kids,
care about them,

11
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:36,855
and be ready to motivate them
to grow and learn.

12
00:01:36,855 --> 00:01:38,530
- Two times two equals?
- Four!

13
00:01:38,530 --> 00:01:40,320
- Two times two?
- Four!

14
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:44,780
But the problem is,
he's not into any of that.

15
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:51,048
And he was sure he wouldn't make it
all the way through as a teacher.

16
00:01:52,228 --> 00:01:55,070
But he made it through,

17
00:01:55,070 --> 00:02:00,384
thanks to another teacher
who was always there to support him.

18
00:02:01,066 --> 00:02:02,280
Snap your fingers!

19
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:05,176
The teacher who taught him

20
00:02:05,176 --> 00:02:09,467
that teachers are no different
from their students.

21
00:02:09,467 --> 00:02:12,648
If students are growing and learning,

22
00:02:12,648 --> 00:02:16,050
then teachers are growing and learning too.

23
00:02:17,315 --> 00:02:20,346
And it's a beautiful journey

24
00:02:20,346 --> 00:02:24,780
when you have someone by your side
through it all.

25
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:37,323
[6 Months Earlier]
Teachers, please keep an eye on the kids.

26
00:02:37,323 --> 00:02:39,383
Thank you. Bye.

27
00:02:39,383 --> 00:02:41,896
Go ahead and cross. Watch out for cars.

28
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:44,678
Hello.

29
00:02:57,640 --> 00:02:59,656
- 10 minutes!
- 15 minutes!

30
00:02:59,656 --> 00:03:00,700
10 minutes!

31
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,112
I think it's 15 minutes!

32
00:03:02,112 --> 00:03:03,114
10 minutes!

33
00:03:03,114 --> 00:03:04,470
No, 15 minutes!

34
00:03:04,470 --> 00:03:05,730
10 minutes!

35
00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:07,478
Trust me. 15 minutes.

36
00:03:07,478 --> 00:03:09,092
I think it's only 10 minutes!

37
00:03:09,092 --> 00:03:12,507
No, I think
it might even be more than 15 minutes.

38
00:03:12,507 --> 00:03:14,802
Hey, Nobel, show your teacher some respect!

39
00:03:14,802 --> 00:03:16,589
Even though Teacher Pobmek's classes
aren't fun,

40
00:03:16,589 --> 00:03:19,760
he's not late every day.

41
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:23,104
Please. Bitcoin, which team are you on?

42
00:03:23,846 --> 00:03:25,738
What do I get if I guess right?

43
00:03:25,738 --> 00:03:27,480
You get all these snacks.

44
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:29,680
[Just a pool for fun. Betting is bad]

45
00:03:30,815 --> 00:03:33,130
Well then, I'm team...

46
00:03:33,130 --> 00:03:43,580
You're late! You're late!

47
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,879
Hey, you up yet?

48
00:04:00,879 --> 00:04:03,252
- Yeah.
- See?

49
00:04:03,252 --> 00:04:05,176
I knew you'd go back to sleep.

50
00:04:05,176 --> 00:04:07,450
I already let you sleep in really late.

51
00:04:07,450 --> 00:04:09,076
Wake up right now!

52
00:04:10,449 --> 00:04:12,270
Shit!

53
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:13,738
I checked the weather forecast.

54
00:04:13,738 --> 00:04:17,215
It's probably going to be really hot today,
so wear lighter colors.

55
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:25,777
You're teaching geometry today.
Don't forget the models.

56
00:04:30,373 --> 00:04:32,950
One last thing. The lollipop.

57
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:35,339
You look the cutest when you smile.

58
00:04:35,339 --> 00:04:37,258
So smile at the kids a lot.

59
00:04:37,258 --> 00:04:40,280
Make sure you leave by 7:30.

60
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,370
Otherwise, you'll be late.

61
00:05:00,681 --> 00:05:01,810
It's 8 now.

62
00:05:01,810 --> 00:05:03,347
Time to close the gate.

63
00:05:03,347 --> 00:05:05,320
Wow, right on the dot, new teacher.

64
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:07,445
It's my first day.
I've got to bring the energy.

65
00:05:07,445 --> 00:05:09,555
- Please take it from here.
- Of course.

66
00:05:09,555 --> 00:05:11,096
Bye.

67
00:05:58,700 --> 00:06:00,680
Yay! It's 15 minutes!

68
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:01,919
Hey, don't cheat!

69
00:06:01,919 --> 00:06:04,138
Teacher Pobmek's 16 minutes late.

70
00:06:04,138 --> 00:06:06,882
Why are you taking it all
for yourself, Nobel?

71
00:06:09,122 --> 00:06:10,120
Hold on.

72
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,800
[Teacher will be late by how many minutes?]
Are you guys gambling?

73
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:15,160
- Do you know it's bad?
- No, he's 15 minutes late.

74
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,755
Look at the clock.

75
00:06:16,755 --> 00:06:19,240
No! I can't read it!

76
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:25,215
Hey!

77
00:06:25,981 --> 00:06:27,390
It's time for class.

78
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:29,398
Go back to your seats.

79
00:06:29,398 --> 00:06:30,877
Kids!

80
00:06:33,774 --> 00:06:35,881
Listen to your teacher!

81
00:06:48,330 --> 00:06:49,840
Fine.

82
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:52,040
You're not going to study, huh?

83
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,582
Then take this!

84
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:18,927
Hi, Principal Sodchuen.

85
00:07:22,530 --> 00:07:25,279
So today, Sodchuen,

86
00:07:25,279 --> 00:07:28,080
I asked the kids to bring candy
to count numbers,

87
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:34,835
because I thought it was tangible
and would help them understand better.

88
00:07:34,835 --> 00:07:37,655
I'm tired of arguing with you, Pobmek.

89
00:07:39,233 --> 00:07:40,760
- You're just so...
- Adorable.

90
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,684
Annoying!

91
00:07:43,677 --> 00:07:45,422
Forget it.

92
00:07:45,422 --> 00:07:48,380
I didn't call you in here to scold you.

93
00:07:48,380 --> 00:07:51,460
I just wanted to introduce you
to our new P.E. teacher.

94
00:07:51,460 --> 00:07:53,920
He said he knows you.

95
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,580
Me?

96
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:56,810
Who is he?

97
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:59,184
Hey, Pobmek!

98
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:05,883
So you two really know each other.

99
00:08:07,037 --> 00:08:10,083
Then I guess
there's no need for an introduction.

100
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:12,630
But how do you know each other?

101
00:08:12,630 --> 00:08:14,157
We were neighbors.

102
00:08:14,157 --> 00:08:16,050
My mom is close friends with his mom,

103
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:18,280
so we grew up close too.

104
00:08:28,090 --> 00:08:30,113
Jee, can you come teach Pobmek for a bit?

105
00:08:30,113 --> 00:08:31,698
Sure, Aunt.

106
00:08:34,292 --> 00:08:36,260
Come on. Let me teach you.

107
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:39,523
What's this?

108
00:08:39,523 --> 00:08:41,686
Why can't you dress neatly like Jee?

109
00:08:41,686 --> 00:08:43,740
- Aunt! Hi!
- Hi.

110
00:08:43,740 --> 00:08:47,437
- How are you?
- Look at him. So neat and clean.

111
00:08:47,437 --> 00:08:49,050
And look at you!

112
00:08:49,050 --> 00:08:51,600
Our kid got a 4.0, honey!

113
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:54,080
Yay!

114
00:09:00,026 --> 00:09:01,330
Nice!

115
00:09:01,330 --> 00:09:02,840
You've been best friends since childhood.

116
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:06,290
You can help each other out with work, okay?

117
00:09:06,290 --> 00:09:09,716
Oh, Pobmek is the one who'll have to help me.

118
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:11,458
I just moved here.

119
00:09:11,458 --> 00:09:13,100
I'll be relying on my friend here a lot.

120
00:09:13,100 --> 00:09:14,717
Well...

121
00:09:14,717 --> 00:09:18,376
I think it might be better
to learn on your own.

122
00:09:29,666 --> 00:09:32,617
Excellent academic performance.

123
00:09:32,617 --> 00:09:34,842
Outstanding record.

124
00:09:34,842 --> 00:09:39,212
Wow. You were born to be a teacher.

125
00:09:39,212 --> 00:09:40,893
You're too kind, Principal.

126
00:09:40,893 --> 00:09:43,174
I'm just lucky.

127
00:09:43,174 --> 00:09:46,272
I pick things up really easily.

128
00:09:46,272 --> 00:09:47,760
I was an early bloomer.

129
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:50,333
"I was an early bloomer".

130
00:09:52,650 --> 00:09:54,570
It's time.

131
00:09:54,570 --> 00:09:57,487
I'm going to go introduce myself
to all the classes now.

132
00:09:57,487 --> 00:09:59,384
Please excuse me.

133
00:10:00,104 --> 00:10:02,181
See you, dude.

134
00:10:09,198 --> 00:10:12,880
He's got that new-teacher energy.

135
00:10:15,466 --> 00:10:17,983
Let's see how long that lasts.

136
00:10:17,983 --> 00:10:19,106
Hey!

137
00:10:19,106 --> 00:10:20,666
Don't tease him.

138
00:10:20,666 --> 00:10:22,640
What about you, huh?

139
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:26,298
Do you still want to be a teacher?

140
00:10:26,872 --> 00:10:30,330
I already told you.

141
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:32,325
I don't want to be a teacher.

142
00:10:32,325 --> 00:10:37,079
And you think I want to be Acting Principal?

143
00:10:37,079 --> 00:10:41,614
Just thinking
about Principal Maximov traveling the world...

144
00:10:41,614 --> 00:10:45,420
makes me want to scream.

145
00:10:50,507 --> 00:10:52,465
What's wrong?

146
00:10:52,465 --> 00:10:56,079
I just felt like screaming, so I did.

147
00:11:02,350 --> 00:11:03,615
Pobmek.

148
00:11:03,615 --> 00:11:04,865
Yes?

149
00:11:04,865 --> 00:11:10,708
You and I are both in a tough spot.

150
00:11:10,708 --> 00:11:16,494
But don't forget
that we all have our responsibilities.

151
00:11:16,494 --> 00:11:18,910
You chose to become a teacher,

152
00:11:19,537 --> 00:11:22,957
no matter what your reason was.

153
00:11:22,957 --> 00:11:26,580
So I want you to do your best.

154
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,290
Do you understand?

155
00:11:32,290 --> 00:11:34,284
Yes, I do.

156
00:11:35,883 --> 00:11:40,280
So, can I go back to my classroom now?

157
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:44,311
Oh, you're rushing back
to teach the kids, aren't you?

158
00:11:44,311 --> 00:11:46,495
I'm going to sneak a peek at my boyfriend.

159
00:11:53,889 --> 00:11:56,468
When I say "Good", you say "morning".

160
00:11:56,468 --> 00:11:58,424
- Good!
- Morning!

161
00:11:58,424 --> 00:12:00,292
- Good!
- Morning!

162
00:12:00,292 --> 00:12:01,798
- Good!
- Morning!

163
00:12:01,798 --> 00:12:03,603
Come on. Good!

164
00:12:03,603 --> 00:12:04,734
Morning!

165
00:12:04,734 --> 00:12:08,132
Yay!

166
00:12:08,132 --> 00:12:11,916
For homeroom today,
I have an amazing mission for you.

167
00:12:11,916 --> 00:12:12,977
And that is...

168
00:12:12,977 --> 00:12:14,088
Is?

169
00:12:14,088 --> 00:12:16,003
- Is...
- Is?

170
00:12:16,003 --> 00:12:17,898
- Is...
- Is?

171
00:12:17,898 --> 00:12:20,171
Writing a card to someone you love!

172
00:12:20,171 --> 00:12:23,415
Yay!

173
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:26,384
Please pass them to the back.

174
00:12:26,384 --> 00:12:29,370
You can write it
to your dad, your mom, or your siblings.

175
00:12:29,370 --> 00:12:30,823
Anyone you love.

176
00:12:30,823 --> 00:12:33,780
Write a card to tell them you love them.

177
00:12:35,943 --> 00:12:37,766
I worked hard on this!

178
00:12:37,766 --> 00:12:39,740
Give it to me!

179
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:41,458
Write your own, King!

180
00:12:41,458 --> 00:12:43,458
I just want to look for a second!

181
00:12:43,458 --> 00:12:45,870
I can't think of anything, Four!

182
00:12:45,870 --> 00:12:49,360
King, let's each write our own card, alright?

183
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:51,280
Let's not copy your friend.

184
00:12:52,658 --> 00:12:55,443
And Four, please speak nicely to your friend,

185
00:12:55,443 --> 00:12:56,977
so he can understand.

186
00:12:56,977 --> 00:12:58,023
Is that okay?

187
00:12:58,023 --> 00:13:01,098
Okay, Teacher Solar.

188
00:13:01,098 --> 00:13:02,423
Good job.

189
00:13:03,911 --> 00:13:06,885
I know you're all working really hard
on your cards,

190
00:13:06,885 --> 00:13:11,220
so I'm sure they're full of love!

191
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:13,820
Yay!

192
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:30,740
I saw you went
to Teacher Sodchuen's office today.

193
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:33,089
What did she get on your case
about this time?

194
00:13:33,089 --> 00:13:35,099
Nothing.

195
00:13:35,099 --> 00:13:37,979
She just told me a new teacher moved here.

196
00:13:37,979 --> 00:13:40,929
He used to be my neighbor.
His name is Jee.

197
00:13:40,929 --> 00:13:42,972
Oh, Teacher Jee.

198
00:13:42,972 --> 00:13:44,788
I saw him this morning.

199
00:13:44,788 --> 00:13:46,489
Yeah, that's him.

200
00:13:46,489 --> 00:13:48,595
He's so damn enthusiastic.

201
00:13:48,595 --> 00:13:51,084
He makes me look bad in comparison.

202
00:13:52,676 --> 00:13:55,098
Then, try to improve yourself a bit.

203
00:13:58,479 --> 00:13:59,760
No!

204
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:02,680
It's too much. I'm tired.

205
00:14:03,310 --> 00:14:04,498
Complaining again.

206
00:14:04,498 --> 00:14:06,924
You complain every day.

207
00:14:06,924 --> 00:14:08,307
It's too much.

208
00:14:08,307 --> 00:14:10,090
You're such a complainer.

209
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:11,510
You complain every day. Jeez.

210
00:14:11,510 --> 00:14:13,176
You're such a complainer.

211
00:14:13,176 --> 00:14:14,649
Wow!

212
00:14:14,649 --> 00:14:18,074
I didn't know my friend had this side to him.

213
00:14:19,941 --> 00:14:23,122
He basically wants the whole world
to know they're dating.

214
00:14:23,122 --> 00:14:24,420
Wait, Principal.

215
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:26,670
You don't want teachers dating each other?

216
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:28,113
I actually think it's a good thing.

217
00:14:28,113 --> 00:14:30,962
They can help each other out.

218
00:14:30,962 --> 00:14:35,500
I think
Pobmek is the only one relying on Solar.

219
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:38,749
If one day Solar isn't around, we're doomed.

220
00:14:38,749 --> 00:14:40,350
Every day. Jeez.

221
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:41,537
I'm not complaining.

222
00:14:41,537 --> 00:14:43,534
You are.

223
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:46,978
But that day will probably never come.

224
00:14:53,661 --> 00:14:55,658
What's up, beautiful?

225
00:14:55,658 --> 00:14:58,870
Oh, what a sweet talker.

226
00:14:58,870 --> 00:15:01,236
What are you making, son?

227
00:15:01,236 --> 00:15:03,707
Chicken breast salad, low calories,

228
00:15:03,707 --> 00:15:08,186
with the salad dressing by Mommy Pranee
that was just delivered to me.

229
00:15:08,186 --> 00:15:11,132
Have you run out?
I can send you some more.

230
00:15:11,132 --> 00:15:12,618
Not yet, Aunt.

231
00:15:12,618 --> 00:15:15,750
It's so good we never seem to finish it.

232
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:18,162
Are you talking about the salad dressing?

233
00:15:20,830 --> 00:15:24,370
By the way, how was teaching the kids
to write cards?

234
00:15:24,370 --> 00:15:26,580
The kids loved it.

235
00:15:26,580 --> 00:15:28,780
I guess
they don't write letters anymore these days,

236
00:15:28,780 --> 00:15:30,420
so they were super excited.

237
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:31,320
Nice.

238
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:34,725
If I come up with any new ideas,
I'll share them with you.

239
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,780
Okay?

240
00:15:36,780 --> 00:15:39,560
Just what I'd expect from a retired teacher
who refuses to retire.

241
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,746
Beautiful.

242
00:15:40,746 --> 00:15:42,480
Of course.

243
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:48,571
Once Teacher Pranee, always Teacher Pranee.

244
00:15:48,571 --> 00:15:52,080
Being a teacher is for life.

245
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:53,120
[Teacher Solar is my hero]

246
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:55,880
[Teacher Solar & Teacher Pobmek]

247
00:16:04,452 --> 00:16:06,720
You're just too cute.

248
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:10,330
After teaching the kids to write letters,
you still have time to write your own.

249
00:16:10,330 --> 00:16:14,779
If your mom reads it, she'll be so happy.

250
00:16:16,290 --> 00:16:19,185
Why don't you write one for your mom?

251
00:16:19,185 --> 00:16:20,947
No way.

252
00:16:20,947 --> 00:16:23,978
My mom's not sweet like yours.

253
00:16:31,339 --> 00:16:33,407
- Let me see.
- Hey, no!

254
00:16:33,407 --> 00:16:34,803
Why not? Let me see.

255
00:16:34,803 --> 00:16:36,070
No! I'm shy.

256
00:16:36,070 --> 00:16:37,301
What do you mean you're shy?

257
00:16:37,301 --> 00:16:39,160
- Let me see.
- I'm shy.

258
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:40,278
No!

259
00:16:40,278 --> 00:16:41,358
Ouch!

260
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:47,730
Shit. What's wrong?

261
00:16:49,006 --> 00:16:51,840
Well...

262
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:53,684
I jumped over...

263
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,862
the school gate again this morning.

264
00:17:17,339 --> 00:17:20,175
How is it? Feeling better?

265
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,085
Come on.

266
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:34,175
Hey, you don't have to.

267
00:17:34,175 --> 00:17:37,250
It's okay. Let me do it for you.

268
00:17:37,250 --> 00:17:38,740
Come on.

269
00:17:49,709 --> 00:17:51,202
Solar.

270
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:55,378
Why are you so good to me?

271
00:17:59,010 --> 00:18:00,490
What's gotten into you?

272
00:18:00,490 --> 00:18:02,575
Why are you being emotional?

273
00:18:03,732 --> 00:18:05,775
I'm not.

274
00:18:07,060 --> 00:18:09,350
I'm just curious.

275
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:11,582
I feel like I'm just a burden.

276
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:15,277
I've never been able
to do anything nice for you.

277
00:18:21,647 --> 00:18:23,676
Not just for you.

278
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:28,951
Not for others. Not for Sodchuen.

279
00:18:28,951 --> 00:18:30,920
Not for the kids either.

280
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:33,178
I'm useless to everyone.

281
00:18:35,182 --> 00:18:39,050
You might not see it yet, but I do.

282
00:18:39,050 --> 00:18:44,904
You're slowly improving in your own way.

283
00:18:57,028 --> 00:18:58,870
Don't cover my eyes.

284
00:18:58,870 --> 00:19:00,820
I'd rather see you.

285
00:19:02,939 --> 00:19:06,452
Sometimes when you can't see with your eyes,

286
00:19:06,452 --> 00:19:08,575
you can see more clearly.

287
00:19:12,699 --> 00:19:14,580
Alright, feet out.

288
00:19:33,658 --> 00:19:35,941
All relaxed now, Teacher?

289
00:19:38,550 --> 00:19:40,432
Okay.

290
00:19:40,432 --> 00:19:44,476
Next, get ready to be punished.

291
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:53,953
I heard you're a bad teacher.

292
00:19:54,770 --> 00:19:56,969
I'm a really bad teacher.

293
00:19:56,969 --> 00:20:00,732
Can I retake the test with you?

294
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:16,960
No. Keep it on.

295
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,675
Not again.

296
00:20:20,393 --> 00:20:22,221
What do you have to do first?

297
00:20:25,329 --> 00:20:29,925
Thank you, Teacher.

298
00:20:43,473 --> 00:20:45,624
Wake up, baby.

299
00:20:45,624 --> 00:20:47,790
Wake up, baby.

300
00:20:47,790 --> 00:20:49,893
Wake up, baby.

301
00:20:49,893 --> 00:20:51,179
Wake up...

302
00:21:14,744 --> 00:21:18,183
Flashcards for teaching the kids vocabulary.

303
00:21:19,620 --> 00:21:23,560
It's not very hot today,
but wear light colors.

304
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:25,679
You look cute in them.

305
00:21:29,490 --> 00:21:33,280
You look the cutest when you smile as well.

306
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:03,520
[Thank you :)
But next time, sleep with a blanket!]

307
00:22:16,015 --> 00:22:18,670
So, you like how I've improved, don't you?

308
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:19,960
Sorry.

309
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:24,164
Is this Mr. Tewtawan Mancharoensin's
emergency contact?

310
00:22:24,781 --> 00:22:26,091
Yes.

311
00:22:26,091 --> 00:22:27,869
I'm his partner.

312
00:22:27,869 --> 00:22:30,275
Please stay calm.

313
00:22:30,275 --> 00:22:32,080
The thing is...

314
00:22:39,698 --> 00:22:40,280
This morning,

315
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:43,428
when Mr. Tewtawan was crossing the road
in front of the school,

316
00:22:43,428 --> 00:22:45,819
he was in an accident.

317
00:23:00,148 --> 00:23:02,326
I'm Tewtawan's partner. How is he?

318
00:23:02,326 --> 00:23:04,114
Please calm down. Well...

319
00:23:04,114 --> 00:23:06,448
I even woke up before him this morning.

320
00:23:07,262 --> 00:23:10,080
But I was so sleepy
and accidentally fell asleep.

321
00:23:11,770 --> 00:23:14,220
If I'd pushed myself more,

322
00:23:14,220 --> 00:23:17,620
I could've taken Solar to school.

323
00:23:17,620 --> 00:23:20,533
Then none of this would've happened.

324
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:29,964
I didn't take good care of my partner.

325
00:23:29,964 --> 00:23:31,627
You did take good care of him.

326
00:23:31,627 --> 00:23:34,080
No! Not well enough!

327
00:23:35,531 --> 00:23:37,040
Alright, if you say so.

328
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,947
But we've been taking good care of him.

329
00:23:38,947 --> 00:23:40,954
Mr. Tewtawan has been awake for a while.

330
00:23:40,954 --> 00:23:43,386
You can go in and see him now.

331
00:23:55,220 --> 00:23:56,676
Solar!

332
00:24:10,940 --> 00:24:14,409
Mr. Tewtawan, you're feeling better, right?

333
00:24:14,409 --> 00:24:16,520
You're so lucky.

334
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:19,080
You got grazed by a car,
hit your head, and passed out,

335
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:21,600
but you look fine.

336
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:23,386
Really?

337
00:24:23,386 --> 00:24:25,820
Have you checked thoroughly?

338
00:24:25,820 --> 00:24:30,264
Well, according to the X-ray results,
there are no broken bones.

339
00:24:30,264 --> 00:24:33,789
The CT scan shows no bleeding in the brain.

340
00:24:33,789 --> 00:24:37,676
He just has a few bruises on his body.

341
00:24:43,158 --> 00:24:47,279
Solar, are you okay?

342
00:24:53,820 --> 00:24:56,123
Are you sure he's okay?

343
00:24:56,123 --> 00:24:58,310
Why does my partner seem a bit off?

344
00:25:02,464 --> 00:25:04,747
Everything looks normal.

345
00:25:04,747 --> 00:25:06,701
He's probably just still in shock.

346
00:25:06,701 --> 00:25:08,927
Do you want to admit him overnight

347
00:25:08,927 --> 00:25:13,000
so we can observe him and put him on an IV?

348
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:14,479
Ouch!

349
00:25:17,445 --> 00:25:19,458
I want to go home now.

350
00:25:19,458 --> 00:25:21,578
Alright then.

351
00:25:36,423 --> 00:25:39,283
You scared the life out of me this morning.

352
00:25:40,556 --> 00:25:45,490
Next time, just wait for me
and be late to school together, okay?

353
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:51,400
Crossing the road in Bangkok
is dangerous as hell.

354
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,852
Hey! What the hell?

355
00:25:53,852 --> 00:25:55,744
Solar! What are you doing?

356
00:25:55,744 --> 00:25:56,873
What are you going to do to me, Uncle?

357
00:25:56,873 --> 00:25:57,830
Huh? Uncle?

358
00:25:57,830 --> 00:25:59,348
Yeah!

359
00:25:59,348 --> 00:26:01,422
What did you put in the water?

360
00:26:01,422 --> 00:26:02,719
I just put water into the cup.

361
00:26:02,719 --> 00:26:03,756
Liar.

362
00:26:03,756 --> 00:26:06,470
You put a sleeping pill in it, didn't you?

363
00:26:06,470 --> 00:26:08,474
A sleeping pill? Why would I do that?

364
00:26:08,474 --> 00:26:11,006
Because you kidnapped me, Uncle!
Uncle Kidnapper!

365
00:26:11,006 --> 00:26:13,279
What Uncle Kidnapper
are you talking about?

366
00:26:14,109 --> 00:26:15,660
And what's that?

367
00:26:16,805 --> 00:26:19,153
Well... handcuffs.

368
00:26:19,153 --> 00:26:21,855
See? You're Uncle Kidnapper!

369
00:26:21,855 --> 00:26:23,048
You're Uncle Kidnapper!

370
00:26:23,048 --> 00:26:24,698
What Uncle Kidnapper
are you talking about, Solar?

371
00:26:24,698 --> 00:26:25,845
My name is not Solar!

372
00:26:25,845 --> 00:26:28,330
Turn me back into my original body right now!

373
00:26:28,330 --> 00:26:31,211
Your original body?
What are you talking about, Solar?

374
00:26:31,211 --> 00:26:33,230
I said my name's not Solar!

375
00:26:33,230 --> 00:26:36,580
If it's not Solar, then what's your name?

376
00:26:42,849 --> 00:26:46,349
I... am... Sun!

377
00:26:47,783 --> 00:26:49,282
Sun?

378
00:26:51,488 --> 00:26:53,984
What the hell are you talking about?

379
00:26:54,760 --> 00:26:56,633
Your name is Solar.

380
00:26:57,575 --> 00:26:59,510
- My name is Sun.
- Solar.

381
00:26:59,510 --> 00:27:00,959
- Sun.
- Solar.

382
00:27:00,959 --> 00:27:02,082
- Sun.
- Solar.

383
00:27:02,082 --> 00:27:03,410
- Sun.
- Solar.

384
00:27:03,410 --> 00:27:04,382
- Sun.
- Solar!

385
00:27:04,382 --> 00:27:06,951
I said it's Sun!

386
00:27:06,951 --> 00:27:08,181
Ouch!

387
00:27:08,181 --> 00:27:09,556
Solar!

388
00:27:09,556 --> 00:27:12,178
Solar, where are you going? Solar!

389
00:27:27,024 --> 00:27:29,899
To use the lift, you need a keycard.

390
00:27:33,670 --> 00:27:35,144
Help! Help!

391
00:27:35,144 --> 00:27:36,180
What's going on?

392
00:27:36,180 --> 00:27:38,260
A kidnapper is trying to kidnap me, Auntie.

393
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:40,956
Excuse me? Did you just call me Auntie?

394
00:27:40,956 --> 00:27:42,361
Please help me, Auntie.

395
00:27:42,361 --> 00:27:45,777
I'm only a few years older than you,
and you're calling me Auntie?

396
00:27:47,181 --> 00:27:49,276
- Let me hide in here, Auntie.
- No.

397
00:27:49,276 --> 00:27:50,809
- Please, Auntie.
- No.

398
00:27:50,809 --> 00:27:52,960
Please, Auntie.

399
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:55,516
Ow, my eyes hurt.

400
00:28:02,719 --> 00:28:06,501
Next time you two want to role-play,
learn to respect your neighbors.

401
00:28:36,441 --> 00:28:40,369
You're saying...

402
00:28:40,369 --> 00:28:43,818
we're really friends, Uncle?

403
00:28:44,456 --> 00:28:46,338
Of course, we are.

404
00:28:48,043 --> 00:28:49,320
You still don't believe me?

405
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:51,055
No.

406
00:28:53,671 --> 00:28:56,756
Why am I in this body?

407
00:28:56,756 --> 00:28:58,779
When did I grow up?

408
00:29:00,367 --> 00:29:02,690
You said your name is Sun, right?

409
00:29:05,255 --> 00:29:06,681
Yeah.

410
00:29:09,810 --> 00:29:11,621
Then let me ask you something.

411
00:29:12,784 --> 00:29:15,460
How old are you, really?

412
00:29:23,633 --> 00:29:25,140
I'm 7.

413
00:29:28,310 --> 00:29:31,200
Why are you taking care of me,
Uncle Kidnapper?

414
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:32,675
You're going to take good care of me first,

415
00:29:32,675 --> 00:29:35,484
and then ask my mom for ransom, right?

416
00:29:37,419 --> 00:29:39,550
I told you, I'm not a kidnapper.

417
00:29:39,550 --> 00:29:42,049
We're friends.

418
00:29:42,049 --> 00:29:44,062
And I'm not asking for any ransom.

419
00:29:44,062 --> 00:29:46,944
Even friends can kidnap each other.

420
00:29:46,944 --> 00:29:48,643
Fine.

421
00:29:48,643 --> 00:29:49,683
Whatever!

422
00:29:49,683 --> 00:29:51,232
But don't act up.

423
00:29:51,232 --> 00:29:52,978
Otherwise, I won't take care of you,

424
00:29:52,978 --> 00:29:55,098
and I'll kick you out.

425
00:30:02,210 --> 00:30:05,822
Stay here. Don't act up. Stay still.

426
00:30:13,380 --> 00:30:16,384
Oh, you got back from the hospital so early.

427
00:30:16,384 --> 00:30:19,425
How's Solar?

428
00:30:19,425 --> 00:30:22,891
Well, Solar...

429
00:30:22,891 --> 00:30:24,477
Wow!

430
00:30:25,180 --> 00:30:27,576
Nice condo, dude.

431
00:30:29,760 --> 00:30:31,300
Teacher Solar is okay now, right?

432
00:30:31,300 --> 00:30:33,582
Yeah, he's fine now.

433
00:30:34,203 --> 00:30:36,667
Thank you so much, Sodchuen, for checking in.

434
00:30:36,667 --> 00:30:39,294
Solar's already asleep.

435
00:30:41,938 --> 00:30:44,286
He's pretty loud when he sleeps, huh?

436
00:30:45,439 --> 00:30:49,418
He tosses and turns in his sleep.

437
00:30:51,966 --> 00:30:55,236
Tossing and turning this much is worrying.

438
00:30:55,236 --> 00:30:57,420
You might want to have him do a sleep study.

439
00:30:57,420 --> 00:31:01,092
Thank you so much
for worrying about my boyfriend.

440
00:31:01,092 --> 00:31:03,564
It's late. Please go home.

441
00:31:03,564 --> 00:31:05,150
- Oh?
- Hey!

442
00:31:05,150 --> 00:31:06,449
Pobmek!

443
00:31:06,449 --> 00:31:10,220
Come on! We came all the way here!

444
00:31:10,220 --> 00:31:11,732
Pobmek!

445
00:31:15,348 --> 00:31:17,105
Hey! What are you doing?

446
00:31:17,105 --> 00:31:18,980
You've made a mess!

447
00:31:20,924 --> 00:31:22,676
Go to sleep.

448
00:31:34,130 --> 00:31:35,356
Hey!

449
00:31:35,356 --> 00:31:37,240
You're going to break the bed!

450
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:39,682
If you want to play,
go play in the other room.

451
00:31:40,740 --> 00:31:42,133
Hey!

452
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:57,476
Hey!

453
00:31:59,027 --> 00:32:01,430
Why are you doing this?

454
00:32:01,430 --> 00:32:02,920
What else do you want?

455
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:05,279
I get tired too, you know!

456
00:32:13,590 --> 00:32:15,812
Didn't you say it yourself, Uncle?

457
00:32:17,070 --> 00:32:18,939
That if I didn't behave,

458
00:32:19,692 --> 00:32:21,657
you'd kick me out.

459
00:32:25,964 --> 00:32:28,421
I want to go home already.

460
00:32:33,727 --> 00:32:35,979
I want to see my mom.

461
00:33:14,089 --> 00:33:15,576
Here.

462
00:33:17,620 --> 00:33:19,780
This is your favorite, right?

463
00:33:31,738 --> 00:33:33,982
I'll call your mom.

464
00:33:36,740 --> 00:33:41,381
But let's do something while we wait.

465
00:33:56,944 --> 00:33:58,784
What do you want to do?

466
00:34:11,620 --> 00:34:13,531
Do you want to read a story?

467
00:34:29,457 --> 00:34:30,980
You can pick.

468
00:34:40,065 --> 00:34:42,423
You picked an English book.

469
00:34:43,531 --> 00:34:46,320
Alright, let Uncle translate it for you.

470
00:34:53,735 --> 00:34:56,325
Once upon a time,

471
00:34:56,325 --> 00:34:59,200
there was a little hedgehog
and a little squirrel.

472
00:34:59,200 --> 00:35:04,180
They lived in the same tree hollow,
but separately.

473
00:35:05,750 --> 00:35:09,780
Then one day, a big storm blew through

474
00:35:09,780 --> 00:35:12,862
and filled the hollow with fallen leaves.

475
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:19,864
At first, they tried cleaning by themselves,

476
00:35:19,864 --> 00:35:21,950
but it was so tiring.

477
00:35:21,950 --> 00:35:24,835
No matter how much they cleaned,
they just couldn't finish it.

478
00:35:25,564 --> 00:35:28,215
So the two of them teamed up

479
00:35:28,215 --> 00:35:34,273
and happily cleaned the tree hollow together.

480
00:36:21,089 --> 00:36:24,165
What? A car grazed him? Oh no!

481
00:36:24,165 --> 00:36:27,031
Where is he now? How is he?

482
00:36:27,031 --> 00:36:28,791
He's okay now, Aunt.

483
00:36:28,791 --> 00:36:30,010
He's safe.

484
00:36:30,010 --> 00:36:32,624
He's back at the condo.

485
00:36:32,624 --> 00:36:34,506
I'm out of town right now,

486
00:36:34,506 --> 00:36:37,550
but I'll go back to Bangkok as soon as I can.

487
00:36:37,550 --> 00:36:40,820
Solar is safe now. Please don't worry.

488
00:36:40,820 --> 00:36:41,895
Really?

489
00:36:41,895 --> 00:36:45,480
If you say so, then I'm relieved.

490
00:36:46,458 --> 00:36:48,405
I'm glad he's fine.

491
00:36:48,405 --> 00:36:50,307
Yes, Aunt.

492
00:36:50,307 --> 00:36:52,174
How's it going over there?

493
00:36:52,174 --> 00:36:55,608
Solar seems comfortable.

494
00:36:55,608 --> 00:36:57,828
He's resting now.

495
00:36:57,828 --> 00:37:02,488
No, I mean you, Pobmek.

496
00:37:02,488 --> 00:37:04,379
How are you?

497
00:37:14,781 --> 00:37:16,815
I...

498
00:37:18,388 --> 00:37:20,082
I'm okay.

499
00:37:20,942 --> 00:37:23,659
Are you really okay?

500
00:37:23,659 --> 00:37:25,680
Yeah, I'm okay.

501
00:37:26,490 --> 00:37:29,433
You must be really shocked and tired.

502
00:37:30,483 --> 00:37:32,575
A little.

503
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:35,513
Pobmek.

504
00:37:35,513 --> 00:37:36,950
Yes?

505
00:37:36,950 --> 00:37:41,187
You know, whenever I'm dealing with
something bad,

506
00:37:41,187 --> 00:37:44,518
I have a trick to feel better.

507
00:37:44,518 --> 00:37:47,179
What's the trick?

508
00:37:53,371 --> 00:37:58,322
Whenever something's bothering me,
I clean the toilet.

509
00:37:58,322 --> 00:38:03,042
Then I sweep and mop the floor.

510
00:38:03,042 --> 00:38:08,255
No matter what I'm worried about,
it all feels lighter.

511
00:38:28,663 --> 00:38:30,079
Hi.

512
00:38:54,950 --> 00:38:56,490
I'm Solar.

513
00:38:56,490 --> 00:38:59,058
Looking forward to living together, roomie.

514
00:39:07,193 --> 00:39:09,508
I'm Pobmek.

515
00:39:09,508 --> 00:39:11,083
Pobmek?

516
00:39:11,806 --> 00:39:13,070
I'm Solar.

517
00:39:13,070 --> 00:39:15,020
Our names are both related to the sky.

518
00:39:24,910 --> 00:39:26,680
Is something stressing you out?

519
00:39:36,620 --> 00:39:42,980
My mom said when something
is stressing you out or worrying you,

520
00:39:42,980 --> 00:39:45,784
there's one thing that can help.

521
00:39:49,902 --> 00:39:51,860
Cleaning the room.

522
00:40:17,621 --> 00:40:18,940
Hey!

523
00:40:19,770 --> 00:40:21,680
What are you doing?

524
00:40:21,680 --> 00:40:23,916
I'm mopping the floor.

525
00:40:23,916 --> 00:40:25,443
Huh?

526
00:40:25,443 --> 00:40:28,458
You need to sweep before you mop.

527
00:40:28,458 --> 00:40:30,559
You mop before you sweep.

528
00:40:30,559 --> 00:40:31,596
Huh?

529
00:40:31,596 --> 00:40:33,235
You sweep before you mop.

530
00:40:33,235 --> 00:40:34,520
You mop before you sweep.

531
00:40:34,520 --> 00:40:36,840
No, you sweep before you mop.

532
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:39,822
My mom taught me to mop first.

533
00:40:41,249 --> 00:40:43,294
We're not getting anywhere
arguing like this.

534
00:40:43,294 --> 00:40:44,490
How about this?

535
00:40:44,490 --> 00:40:45,870
Let's have a staring contest.

536
00:40:45,870 --> 00:40:47,560
Whoever blinks first loses.

537
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:51,099
The loser has to do
what the winner says, okay?

538
00:40:56,278 --> 00:40:57,739
Fine.

539
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:08,230
Don't cheat.

540
00:41:08,230 --> 00:41:09,981
Only use your eyes.

541
00:41:33,883 --> 00:41:36,190
What are we even doing?

542
00:41:36,190 --> 00:41:38,859
At this rate,
we'll never get to sweep or mop.

543
00:41:41,050 --> 00:41:45,480
At least...
you're not stressed anymore, right?

544
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:23,320
[Pobmek, you know what?]

545
00:42:23,320 --> 00:42:25,000
[The first day I moved into the dorm,]

546
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:26,720
[I was so worried
about whether I'd get along with my roommate]

547
00:42:30,870 --> 00:42:35,018
Pobmek, you know what?

548
00:42:36,260 --> 00:42:39,218
The first day I moved into the dorm,

549
00:42:39,218 --> 00:42:43,880
I was so worried
about whether I'd get along with my roommate.

550
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:46,280
[Student Dormitory, Tanapak Building]

551
00:42:52,926 --> 00:42:57,578
But when I met you, I knew...

552
00:42:57,578 --> 00:43:00,378
I wasn't the only one who was worried.

553
00:43:01,534 --> 00:43:05,620
So whatever you're worried about,

554
00:43:05,620 --> 00:43:10,180
you'll always have me by your side.

555
00:43:11,937 --> 00:43:13,732
I love you.

556
00:43:37,965 --> 00:43:40,526
I love you too, Solar.

557
00:44:48,452 --> 00:44:50,340
Hey!

558
00:44:50,340 --> 00:44:51,543
Have you seen my boyfriend?

559
00:44:51,543 --> 00:44:53,770
Hey, I just clocked in.

560
00:44:53,770 --> 00:44:55,170
How could I have seen him?

561
00:44:55,170 --> 00:44:59,581
Can you call and ask your friend
who worked the shift before you?

562
00:45:03,819 --> 00:45:05,544
Can you hurry up?

563
00:45:05,544 --> 00:45:08,420
Relax, I'm checking.

564
00:45:09,333 --> 00:45:12,880
Pobmek, what's going on?

565
00:45:14,100 --> 00:45:15,931
What are you doing here?

566
00:45:18,823 --> 00:45:20,349
Oh.

567
00:45:20,349 --> 00:45:22,376
Why aren't you wearing shoes?

568
00:45:22,376 --> 00:45:24,379
You could hurt your feet.

569
00:45:38,940 --> 00:45:42,606
But even when we have someone we love
by our side,

570
00:45:42,606 --> 00:45:47,579
getting to the point of learning
isn't easy at all.

571
00:45:48,370 --> 00:45:51,450
There are still many obstacles

572
00:45:51,450 --> 00:45:54,174
that can test us at any time,

573
00:45:55,007 --> 00:45:57,300
both from within ourselves...

574
00:45:58,160 --> 00:46:00,578
and even from the ones we love.

575
00:46:08,512 --> 00:46:11,400
This story isn't over yet.

576
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:13,970
It's only just the beginning.

577
00:46:27,340 --> 00:46:29,291
Wake up, Teacher.

578
00:46:29,291 --> 00:46:31,875
- Uncle Kidnapper.
- Sun?

579
00:46:31,875 --> 00:46:34,551
- No, I'm going home to see my mom!
- Sun, come back here!

580
00:46:34,551 --> 00:46:37,723
A teacher at the main campus
is acting strangely.

581
00:46:37,723 --> 00:46:39,457
There you are.

582
00:46:40,067 --> 00:46:41,313
No, I'm leaving!

583
00:46:41,313 --> 00:46:43,182
It's some kind of mental health issue.

584
00:46:46,551 --> 00:46:48,254
Don't worry.

585
00:46:48,254 --> 00:46:50,817
I'm going to help you recover,
no matter what.

